  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Families of low income or the elderly</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">On October 29, 2012, Hurricane Sandy slammed into the northeast coast of the United States, taking 139 lives and leaving thousands of families displaced or homeless. IRT has been working for almost four years in some of the hardest hit areas of New Jersey, in partnership with A Future With Hope. 

Disaster recovery is a long-term process, and IRT prides itself on supporting affected communities even after the cameras leave. For instance, after Hurricane Katrina (2005), IRT deployed teams every other month to the Mississippi coast through March 2012, rebuilding and repairing 219 homes of the poor and elderly that were damaged or destroyed.  In 2016, IRT is sending six teams throughout the year to New Jersey to continue to support recovery efforts.</narrative>
  </description>
